radiographic_examinations.findings: No acute hemorrhage or acute vascular territorial infarction. No mass, mass effect, edema or shift of normally midline structures. The ventricles and sulci are largely prominent in size and configuration, due to global parenchymal involutional change age related. There is periventricular white matter hypodensities, consistent with chronic small vessel ischemic disease. There are no osseous abnormalities noted.
